== Title ==
Is it necessary to have "Leningrad" in the article's name? [[User:Toccata quarta|Toccata quarta]] ([[User talk:Toccata quarta|talk]]) 05:27, 2 May 2013 (UTC) :Yes. This wasn't the world première, but it was significant as the first time the symphony was played in "its" city. Several sources use the term "Leningrad première" for the concert (examples [http://www.historyinanhour.com/2011/08/09/the-leningrad-symphony-summary/][http://www.shostakovich.com/may2002.html][http://www.naxos.com/mainsite/blurbs_reviews.asp?item_code=8.573057&catNum=573057&filetype=About%20this%20Recording&language=English]). [[User:Nikkimaria|Nikkimaria]] ([[User talk:Nikkimaria|talk]]) 13:02, 2 May 2013 (UTC)
